dth: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;" loading="lazy" alt="JEE Advanced 2019 Paper 2 Offline Chemistry - p-Block Elements Question 40 English Explanation 2"> <br><br>Thus, option (b) is correct.<br><br>When Zn is react with conc. NaOH then H<sub>2</sub> gas is evolved and Na<sub>2</sub>ZnO<sub>2</sub> is obtained.<br><br>$$Zn + 2NaOH(conc.)\mathrel{\mathop{\kern0pt\longrightarrow}
